<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;"><i>By Curtis Houck</i></p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;"><a style=3D"color: #2b63cb; text-decoration: none=
;" href=3D"http://email.mrc.org/c/13zPkxrMxLZKFo1cvylunXN" target=3D"_blank=
">Following the lead</a> of ABC and CBS from Thursday morning, <i>NBC Night=
ly News</i> cheered President Barack Obama&rsquo;s newest initiative that w=
ould require private businesses <b>&ldquo;to guarantee&rdquo; </b>their emp=
loyees <b>&ldquo;at least seven&rdquo; </b>paid sick days and affect 43 mil=
lion Americans, with Chris Jansing forwarding a tired liberal talking point=
: "The U.N. says only the U.S. and Papua New Guinea don't have some mandato=
ry paid time off for new moms."</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">While senior White House correspondent Jansing in=
terviewed the owner of a Maryland carpet company opposed to the President&r=
squo;s proposal, she had three quotes (compared to one from the business ow=
ner) from someone she failed to disclose as more than just a woman in favor=
 of the policy since she was fired from her job for taking time off to have=
 her daughter.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px; text-align: center;"><br><a style=3D"color: #2b63c=
b; text-decoration: none;" href=3D"http://email.mrc.org/c/13zPw3N5D6eBRuaYB=
FOACTK"><img style=3D"max-width: 100=3D"http://msgfocus.com/files/amf_paramount/workspace_7/icon_play_25x25.png=
" alt=3D""><span style=3D"font-size: 24px;">View video on MRCTV</span></a><=
/p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">Turns out, the woman who Jansing had interviewed =
<a style=3D"color: #2b63cb; text-decoration: none;" href=3D"http://email.mr=
c.org/c/13zPHA8oIqtt3AkKHNhGRPH" target=3D"_blank">appeared and spoken</a> =
at an October 2013 event in Landover, Maryland with liberal Congresswomen N=
ancy Pelosi (Calif.), Donna Edwards (Md.) and Senator Barbara Mikulski (Md.=
).</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">According to C-SPAN, the event was hosted by Edwa=
rd and promoted <b>&ldquo;the importance of paid sick leave and affordable =
heath insurance and child care.&rdquo;</b></p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">Returning to Jansing&rsquo;s story, she touted a =
United Nations statistic that <b>&ldquo;only the U.S. and Papua New Guinea =
don't have some mandatory paid time off for new moms&rdquo;</b> and the Whi=
te House talking point that <b>&ldquo;43 million private sector workers are=
n't eligible for a single sick day.&rdquo;</b></p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">She later fretted that <b>&ldquo;small business g=
roups are fighting&rdquo; </b>this proposal and since <b>&ldquo;[m]any Repu=
blicans&rdquo;</b> also oppose it, Obama&rsquo;s plan faces <b>&ldquo;an up=
hill battle in Congress.&rdquo;</b></p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">In contrast, the <i>CBS Evening News</i> offered =
a more balanced segment that did not feature a covert liberal activist but =
instead equal soundbites from a woman in favor of the measure whose expecti=
ng a baby and Republican Congresswoman Martha Roby (Ala.), who is opposed t=
o the President&rsquo;s plan but proposed her own plan (that passed the Hou=
se in 2013).</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">CBS News chief White House correspondent Major Ga=
rrett reported that Roby&rsquo;s plan wouldn&rsquo;t have a federal mandate=
 and instead <b>&ldquo;allow employees and employers to trade overtime hour=
s for either pay or time off.&rdquo;</b></p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">Further, Jansing&rsquo;s segment failed to cite a=
ny cost estimate for both Obama&rsquo;s executive action affecting the fede=
ral workforce as well as his plan for private businesses (which would requi=
re approval from Congress).</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">CBS&rsquo;s Garrett did highlight those two stati=
stics at the end of his story with the plan for<b> &ldquo;federal leave&rdq=
uo;</b> being <b>&ldquo;about $250 billion a year&rdquo;</b> and the estima=
ted cost for the private sector being about <b>&ldquo;$2.5 billion every ye=
ar.&rdquo;</b></p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">The relevant portions of the transcript from <i>N=
BC Nightly News</i> on January 15 is transcribed below.</p>
<blockquote>
