<h4 class=3D"inline" style=3D"font-size: 20px; font-weight: 500; margin-bot=
tom: 15px; color: #000; font-family: 'HelveticaNeue-Light', 'Helvetica Neue=
 Light', 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, 'Lucida Grande', sans-serif; l=
ine-height: 1.1; margin: 0; padding: 0;"><a style=3D"font-size: 20px; font-=
weight: 500; margin-bottom: 5px; color: #2b63cb; text-decoration: none;" hr=
ef=3D"http://email.mrc.org/c/13zPT6tHNKIkfGuwNUKN6LE">ABC and CBS Morning S=
hows Help Boost Obama&rsquo;s &lsquo;Paid Sick Leave&rsquo; Mandate</a></h4>
</td>
</tr>

</table>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;"><i>By Jeffrey Meyer</i></p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">On Thursday, ABC&rsquo;s <i>Good Morning America<=
/i> and <i>CBS This Morning</i> eagerly promoted President Obama&rsquo;s la=
test proposal that would require all private companies provide their employ=
ees with &ldquo;at least seven days of paid sick leave.&rdquo; NBC&rsquo;s =
<i>Today </i>did not cover President Obama&rsquo;s initiative on their Thur=
sday morning broadcast.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">During the network coverage of Obama&rsquo;s init=
iative,<b> <i>GMA </i>co-host Robin Roberts cheered on the program and insi=
sted that &ldquo;studies have shown again and again and again that paid sic=
k leave, not only benefits workers and their families but employers, as wel=
l, because productivity goes up.&rdquo; </b></p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px; text-align: center;"><br><a style=3D"color: #2b63c=
b; text-decoration: none;" href=3D"http://email.mrc.org/c/13zQ4CP0T4XbrMEiU=
2dTlHB"><img style=3D"max-width: 100=3D"http://msgfocus.com/files/amf_paramount/workspace_7/icon_play_25x25.png=
" alt=3D""><span style=3D"font-size: 24px;">View video on MRCTV</span></a><=
/p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">On<i> CBS This Morning</i>, co-host Norah O&rsquo=
;Donnell provided a 30-second news brief that sounded like an Obama adminis=
tration press release with no mention of those who oppose a new federal man=
date on private companies:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;"><img class=3D"image-blog_body-100" style=3D"max-w=
idth: 100les/styles/blog_body-100/s3/images/CBSobama_2.jpg?itok=3DI0QoWk0k" alt=3D""=
 width=3D"300" height=3D"169">Today, President Obama will call on Congress =
to guarantee paid sick leave for American workers. The Healthy Families Act=
 would allow employees to earn up to seven paid days off for illness each y=
ear. The president wants Congress to spend $2.2 billion to help states deve=
lop paid leave programs. He will also take executive action signing a presi=
dential memo to give at least six weeks of paid time off for federal worker=
s with a new child. The White House says there are 43 million private secto=
r workers that can't take a sick day without losing pay.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">Over on ABC, Robin Roberts began the network&rsqu=
o;s coverage by hyping &ldquo;a major new initiative for families from the =
White House this morning. President Obama proposing new legislation that wo=
uld require companies to give workers paid sick leave.&rdquo;</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">The <i>GMA </i>co-anchor then turned to Jonathan =
Karl, ABC News Chief White House Correspondent, who, unlike CBS&rsquo;s Nor=
ah O&rsquo;Donnell, actually included Republican criticism of President Oba=
ma&rsquo;s latest mandate:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">This will be an uphill battle, to say the least. =
Republicans don't like the idea of imposing an expensive new regulation on =
companies, on employers. And Robin, Democrats have been trying to pass this=
 bill since 2005. As you can imagine it won't be any easier now that Republ=
icans are in control of both the House and Senate.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">Roberts concluded the segment by giving one final=
 endorsement for Obama&rsquo;s mandated &ldquo;paid sick leave&rdquo; propo=
sal:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">And studies have shown again and again and again =
that paid sick leave, not only benefits workers and their families but empl=
oyers, as well, because productivity goes up.<b> And you heard Jon mention =
about 43 million Americans don't have paid sick leave. How many times does =
Dr. Besser say if you're sick, stay home? Well all these Americans are sayi=
ng we can't stay home because we won't get paid. </b></p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">See relevant transcripts below.</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;"><img class=3D"image-blog_body-100" style=3D"max-w=
idth: 100les/styles/blog_body-100/s3/images/ABCroberts_0.jpg?itok=3DMtqnluHe" alt=3D=
"" width=3D"300" height=3D"169">ABC&rsquo;s <i>Good Morning America</i></p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">January 15, 2015</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">ROBIN ROBERTS: Now to a major new initiative for =
families from the White House this morning. President Obama proposing new l=
egislation that would require companies to give workers paid sick leave. AB=
C's Jonathan Karl is at the White House this morning. Good morning, Jon.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">JONATHAN KARL: Good morning, Robin. The White Hou=
se says some 43 million workers in the United States don't have any paid si=
ck leave at all, so the president is calling on Congress to pass a law that=
 would require companies to give at least seven days of paid sick leave to =
their employees. He's also asking for $2 billion to be given to the states =
and cities to help them pass or start their own programs with family and me=
dical leave. And he's acting on his own making it easier for federal employ=
ees to get up to six weeks of maternity leave. The president is promising a=
 big push on all of this beginning next week, Robin, with the State of the =
Union address.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">ROBERTS: The big question, how much of a chance d=
oes this have to pass, Jon?</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">KARL: Well, this will be an uphill battle, to say=
 the least. Republicans don't like the idea of imposing an expensive new re=
gulation on companies, on employers. And Robin, Democrats have been trying =
to pass this bill since 2005. As you can imagine it won't be any easier now=
 that Republicans are in control of both the House and Senate.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">ROBERTS: Alright Jon thank you very much. And stu=
dies have shown again and again and again that paid sick leave, not only be=
nefits workers and their families but employers, as well, because productiv=
ity goes up. And you heard Jon mention about 43 million Americans don't hav=
e paid sick leave. How many times does Dr. Besser say if you're sick, stay =
home? Well all these Americans are saying we can't stay home because we won=
't get paid.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">STEPHANOPOULOS: We&rsquo;ll lose our job.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">ROBERTS: Right, we&rsquo;ll see.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">STEPHANOPOULOS: Important stuff. Okay Robin thank=
s.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;"><img class=3D"image-blog_body-100" style=3D"max-w=
idth: 100les/styles/blog_body-100/s3/images/CBSodonnell_1.jpg?itok=3DmCHv2dKc" alt=
=3D"" width=3D"300" height=3D"169"><i>CBS This Morning </i></p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">January 15, 2015</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">NORAH O&rsquo;DONNELL: Today, President Obama wil=
l call on Congress to guarantee paid sick leave for American workers. The H=
ealthy Families Act would allow employees to earn up to seven paid days off=
 for illness each year. The president wants Congress to spend $2.2 billion =
to help states develop paid leave programs. He will also take executive act=
ion signing a presidential memo to give at least six weeks of paid time off=
 for federal workers with a new child. The White House says there are 43 mi=
llion private sector workers that can't take a sick day without losing pay.=
</p>
</blockquote>
