<td valign=3D"top"><span class=3D"cyber-index" style=3D"color: #a60000; fon=
t-size: 58px; font-weight: bold; padding-right: 10px;">4</span></td>
<td>
<h4 class=3D"inline" style=3D"font-size: 20px; font-weight: 500; margin-bot=
tom: 15px; color: #000; font-family: 'HelveticaNeue-Light', 'Helvetica Neue=
 Light', 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, 'Lucida Grande', sans-serif; l=
ine-height: 1.1; margin: 0; padding: 0;"><a style=3D"font-size: 20px; font-=
weight: 500; margin-bottom: 5px; color: #2b63cb; text-decoration: none;" hr=
ef=3D"http://email.mrc.org/c/13zQDbQW93FL257DcoDc4vs">Andrea Mitchell Hails=
 Changes in Trade &amp; Travel with Cuba: &lsquo;The Cold War Will Be Over&=
rsquo; on Friday</a></h4>
</td>
</tr>

</table>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;"><i>By Curtis Houck</i></p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">During Thursday&rsquo;s <i>NBC Nightly News</i>, =
NBC News chief foreign affairs correspondent Andrea Mitchell enthusiastical=
ly promoted the new and<b> &ldquo;dramatic changes&rdquo;</b> set to go int=
o effect on Friday that will allow Americans to more easily trade with and =
travel to/from Cuba as causing the Cold War to end.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">In leading off her report, Mitchell announced to =
viewers: <b>&ldquo;In Havana, dramatic change after more than a half-centur=
y. Tomorrow the Cold War will be over. A huge opening for U.S. and Cuban tr=
avel and trade.&rdquo;</b></p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px; text-align: center;"><br><a style=3D"color: #2b63c=
b; text-decoration: none;" href=3D"http://email.mrc.org/c/13zQOIcfenUCebhpi=
w6ijrp"><img style=3D"max-width: 100=3D"http://msgfocus.com/files/amf_paramount/workspace_7/icon_play_25x25.png=
" alt=3D""><span style=3D"font-size: 24px;">View video on MRCTV</span></a><=
/p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">She went on to outline the many changes that Amer=
icans will be able to take advantage of, with a few examples being able to =
travel more easily without a special permit, using a credit card in Cuba, a=
nd being allowed to bring back up to $100 in Cuban cigars.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">At only two points in the entire two-minute-and-4=
3-second segment was there any criticism or opposing viewpoint. While intro=
ducing Mitchell&rsquo;s report, anchor Brian Williams stated that <b>&ldquo=
;questions remain over whether Cuba is truly ready for all of this, ready f=
or the influx.&rdquo;</b></p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">At the conclusion of her story, Mitchell finally =
brought up the <b>&ldquo;critics&rdquo;</b> of this decision by the Obama a=
dministration: <b>&ldquo;Critics say the President is going too far violati=
ng the embargo and many ask whether Cuba is really ready for the American e=
conomic invasion, especially internet access for all Cubans.&rdquo;</b></p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">Fellow broadcast networks ABC and CBS also covere=
d this news, but only in the form of news briefs. On ABC&rsquo;s <i>World N=
ews Tonight</i>, anchor David Muir said that the changes will take place <b=
>&ldquo;just weeks after lifting the embargo in place since the Cold War.&r=
dquo; </b></p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">The problem with that statement, however, is that=
 the embargo technically remains in effect and can only be lifted through a=
n act of Congress. Credit does go out the <i>CBS Evening News</i> for point=
ing out this key fact during its news brief.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">The relevant portions of the transcript from segm=
ent that aired on <i>NBC Nightly News</i> on January 15 are transcribed bel=
ow.</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;"><i>NBC Nightly News</i><br> January 15, 2015<br> =
7:05 p.m. Eastern</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;"><img class=3D"image-blog_body-50" style=3D"max-wi=
dth: 100//newsbusters.org/s3/files/styles/blog_body-50/s3/images/2015-01-15-NBC-NN-=
Cuba1.JPG?itok=3Do4B9lCgl" alt=3D"" width=3D"280">[ON-SCREEN HEADLINE: New =
Era]</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">WILLIAMS: The gateway to Cuba closed to Americans=
 for more than five decades now appears to be swinging open. Starting tomor=
row, and thanks to a change announced today, street scenes in Havana like t=
his one that we're looking at live tonight, may soon be full of American to=
urists, but questions remain over whether Cuba is truly ready for all of th=
is, ready for the influx. Our report on that tonight from our chief foreign=
