<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;"><i>By Matthew Balan</i></p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;"><img style=3D"max-width: 100in-left: 3px; margin-right: 3px;" src=3D"http://www.mrc.org/sites/default/f=
iles/2015-01-15-CNN-ND-Pereira.jpg" alt=3D"" width=3D"280" height=3D"158">A=
s of 6 pm Eastern on Thursday, CNN has devoted <b>just 19 seconds</b> of ai=
r time to the release of five prisoners from Guantanamo Bay detention facil=
ities &ndash; a news brief during the <i>New Day</i> program. This is still=
 more coverage than CBS and NBC, as both Big Three networks ignored the sto=
ry on their Thursday morning newscasts. ABC gave a <a style=3D"color: #2b63=
cb; text-decoration: none;" href=3D"http://email.mrc.org/c/13zRnheaumDbOtKJ=
ASvB2fg" target=3D"_blank">16-second news brief</a> on <i>Good Morning Amer=
ica</i>.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">Anchor Michaela Pereira gave the news brief 11 mi=
nutes into the 7 am Eastern hour of the CNN morning show: [<b>video below</=
b>]</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">MICHAELA PEREIRA: Five Yemeni inmates held at Gua=
ntanamo Bay have been transferred overseas &ndash; at least six years after=
 the Pentagon cleared them for release. Four will go to Oman; one to Estoni=
a. That leaves 122 prisoners at the facility in Cuba. This move has angered=
 some members of Congress, who argue Guantanamo is needed to detain terror =
suspects.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px; text-align: center;"><br><a style=3D"color: #2b63c=
b; text-decoration: none;" href=3D"http://email.mrc.org/c/13zRyNztzGS30zUvG=
ZYHhbd"><img style=3D"max-width: 100=3D"http://msgfocus.com/files/amf_paramount/workspace_7/icon_play_25x25.png=
" alt=3D""><span style=3D"font-size: 24px;">View video on MRCTV</span></a><=
/p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">Correspondent Chloe Summers gave further details =
about the prisoner transfer in a <a style=3D"color: #2b63cb; text-decoratio=
n: none;" href=3D"http://email.mrc.org/c/13zRKjUMF16UcG4hN7rNw7a" target=3D=
"_blank">Thursday item</a> on CNN.com:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">Al Khadr Abdallah Muhammad Al Yafi, Fadel Hussein=
 Saleh Hentif, Abd Al-Rahman Abdullah Au Shabati and Mohammed Ahmed Salam w=
ere sent to Oman. Akhmed Abdul Qadir was transferred to Estonia....</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">The detainees were not released to their home cou=
ntry of Yemen because the government there -- under pressure from al Qaeda =
and Houthi militants -- <b>cannot ensure they won't join al Qaeda elements<=
/b>. The United States has been trying to find countries to take on the det=
ainees who will provide security and human rights assurances for them.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">There are currently 122 prisoners left at Guantan=
amo Bay, including <b>79 Yemeni men</b>, according to documents from the Pe=
ntagon and Joint Task Force Guantanamo....</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">The transfer is part of the White House's ongoing=
 effort to close the Guantanamo Bay detention center. President Barack Obam=
a stated in an interview on CNN's "State of the Union" back in December tha=
t he's "<b>going to be doing everything I can to close it</b>."</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">Neither CNN's on-air reporting nor its online rep=
orting explained which members of Congress opposed the further release of d=
etainees.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">On Thursday, The Hill's <a style=3D"color: #2b63c=
b; text-decoration: none;" href=3D"http://email.mrc.org/c/13zRVQg5KllLoMe3T=
eUTL37" target=3D"_blank">Martin Matishak reported</a> that Republican Cong=
ressman Mac Thornberry, "the new chairman of the House Armed Services Commi=
ttee...said lawmakers should act to prevent President Obama from releasing =
more prisoners from Guantanamo Bay, Cuba." Matishak also noted that "Senate=
 Armed Services Committee chairman John McCain (R-Ariz.) and GOP panel memb=
ers Sens. Kelly Ayotte (N.H.) and Lindsey Graham (S.C.), rolled out legisla=
tion that would prohibit the president from transferring more detainees out=
 of Cuba."</p>
