 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">The media&rsquo;s obsession with the Kennedys rea=
red its ugly head once again on Thursday when <i>CBS This Morning </i>spent=
 four minutes of its broadcast obsessing over newly released letters from J=
acqueline Kennedy written to her favorite fashion designers.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">While all three CBS hosts beamed at Kennedy&rsquo=
;s &ldquo;flair for fashion&rdquo; it was her supposed love of peanut butte=
r and jelly sandwiches that received the most attention with<b> co-host Gay=
le King proclaiming that &ldquo;there&rsquo;s something cool knowing that s=
he ate peanut butter and jelly. I like that.&rdquo;</b></p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px; text-align: center;"><br><a style=3D"color: #2b63c=
