h made her very excited. Onassis was often very hands-on during the process=
.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">HAMILTON: We would have lunch at my desk and she =
would pull out a peanut butter and jelly sandwich that she carried in her b=
ag and have coffee.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;"><img class=3D"image-blog_body-100" style=3D"max-w=
idth: 100les/styles/blog_body-100/s3/images/CBSkennedy.jpg?itok=3D-8kIE5Y6" alt=3D""=
 width=3D"300" height=3D"169">ARENAS: Richard Keith Langham decorated sever=
al of Onassis&rsquo; homes.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">RICHARD KEITH LANGHAM: She had a hand in everythi=
ng there. I mean, whether she would be dictating exactly what sort of velve=
t she wanted on a chair, exactly what sort of cording she wanted to trim a =
pillow.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">ARENAS: In one note Onassis told him &ldquo;I was=
n't mad about the black chairs. Too heavy I'm afraid. Do keep looking.&rdqu=
o; But most of the letters, many written in her signature blue stationery w=
ere actually thank-you notes to both men letting them know how happy she wa=
s with the results. She thanked these designers over and over, she was almo=
st humble.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">BACA: All these notes are special in the sense th=
at she took the time to sit down and write something in appreciation. It wa=
s -- a thank-you note is a form of respect.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">ARENAS: Onassis had other ways to show she was gr=
ateful.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">LANGHAM: She gave me an original 1963 edition of =
her White House guide book, and she inscribed that to me that &ldquo;perhap=
s this great house will know your touch one day&rdquo; and as a young decor=
ator that was sort of awe-inspiring for me.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">ARENAS: 14 photos taken by Bob Davidoff, a longti=
me photographer for the Kennedy family are also part of the auction. Who wo=
uld want these letters and photographs and sketches?</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">BACA: You. Wouldn't you want them?</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">ARENAS: They&rsquo;d be cool to have at my house.=
</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">BACA: Absolutely.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">ARENAS: I can&rsquo;t afford them.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">BACA: Everybody, I mean, I can't imagine anyone w=
ho wouldn't want them.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">ARENAS: More than a thousand people are expected =
to take part. Each lot, some containing 2 to 3 letters is said to be worth =
$800-$1200. Although some would probably argue Onassis' gratitude is pricel=
ess. For <i>CBS This Morning</i>, Vicente Arenas, West Palm Beach, Florida.=
</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">GAYLE KING: Such a class act. I was so sorry I ne=
ver got a chance to meet her. You did.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">CHARLIE ROSE: Yes.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">KING: I was very sorry about that. What was she l=
ike, Charlie? I mean really?</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">ROSE: Charming and just exciting to talk to. Inte=
resting. Had great insights about...I remember we were sitting and she was =
saying I hope the people that work for Jack won't go into the Clinton gover=
nment, you know? She thought that they should be a new breed of people to c=
ome to work.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">O&rsquo;DONNELL: Did you ever see her pull a pean=
ut butter and jelly sandwich out of her purse?</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">KING: There's something cool knowing that she did=
 that.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">ROSE: Although she did invite me once to have lun=
ch in the park.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">KING: There&rsquo;s something cool knowing that s=
he ate peanut butter and jelly. I like that.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">O&rsquo;DONNELL: One of my favorites indeed.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.6; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">&nbsp;</p>
</td>
</tr>

